#Unveiling the Android App Market

Analyzed Google Play Store data to understand app market dynamics.

# Datasets
- apps.csv: 9659 apps with ratings, installs, pricing data
- user_reviews.csv: 64295 user reviews with sentiment

# What I did
- Cleaned data (removed duplicates, fixed Installs and Price columns)
- Explored app category distribution
- Analyzed ratings, free vs paid apps
- Found top categories by installs
- Analyzed user review sentiments

# Key Findings
- Family and Game categories have most apps
- 92% apps are Free
- Communication apps have highest installs
- Most user reviews are Positive

# Tools Used
Python, Pandas, Matplotlib, Seaborn
